title: Emily Remler August 1989
description: Nice interview with guitarist Emily Remler when she was in Minneapolis to play the Jazz Party, which was an annual event sponsored by the Mckenzie and Stephens families during the 1980's.   She talks about her admiration for Wes Montgomery in depth and her take on the evolution of jazz guitar styles.  Sadly poignant because she would die within a year of this interview at the age of 32.
